{{redirect|Relaxor|the hair treatment|Relaxer}}

'''Relaxor ferroelectrics''' are [[ferroelectric]] materials that exhibit high [[electrostriction]]. {{As of|2015}}, although they have been studied for over fifty years,<ref>{{Cite journal | doi = 10.1007/s10853-005-5915-7| title = Recent progress in relaxor ferroelectrics with perovskite structure| journal = Journal of Materials Science| volume = 41| issue = 1| pages = 31| year = 2006| last1 = Bokov | first1 = A. A.| last2 = Ye | first2 = Z. -G. |bibcode = 2006JMatS..41...31B }}</ref> the mechanism for this effect is still not completely understood, and is the subject of continuing research.<ref>{{Cite journal | doi = 10.1103/PhysRevLett.110.147602| title = Anisotropic Local Correlations and Dynamics in a Relaxor Ferroelectric| journal = Physical Review Letters| volume = 110| issue = 14| year = 2013| last1 = Takenaka | first1 = H. | last2 = Grinberg | first2 = I. | last3 = Rappe | first3 = A. M. |arxiv = 1212.0867 |bibcode = 2013PhRvL.110n7602T | pmid=25167037 | page=147602}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|last=Ganesh|first=P.|last2=Cockayne|first2=E.|last3=Ahart|first3=M.|last4=Cohen|first4=R. E.|last5=Burton|first5=B.|last6=Hemley|first6=Russell J.|last7=Ren|first7=Yang|last8=Yang|first8=Wenge|last9=Ye|first9=Z.-G.|date=2010-04-05|title=Origin of diffuse scattering in relaxor ferroelectrics|journal=Physical Review B|volume=81|issue=14|pages=144102|doi=10.1103/PhysRevB.81.144102|arxiv=0908.2373|bibcode=2010PhRvB..81n4102G}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|last=Phelan|first=Daniel|last2=Stock|first2=Christopher|last3=Rodriguez-Rivera|first3=Jose A.|last4=Chi|first4=Songxue|last5=Leão|first5=Juscelino|last6=Long|first6=Xifa|last7=Xie|first7=Yujuan|last8=Bokov|first8=Alexei A.|last9=Ye|first9=Zuo-Guang|year=1754|title=Role of random electric fields in relaxors|url=http://www.pnas.org/content/111/5/1754|journal=Proceedings of the National Academy of Sciences|language=en|volume=111|issue=5|pages=1754–1759|doi=10.1073/pnas.1314780111|issn=0027-8424|pmid=24449912|pmc=3918832|arxiv=1405.2306|bibcode=2014PNAS..111.1754P}}</ref>

Examples of relexor ferroelectrics include:{{Citation needed|date=April 2015}}
* [[lead magnesium niobate]] (PMN)
* [[lead magnesium niobate-lead titanate]] (PMN-PT)
* [[lead lanthanum zirconate titanate]] (PLZT)
* [[lead scandium niobate]] (PSN)

